                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Hey Fly,<br /><br />When I'm having fun, I sometimes find myself forgetting to pay attention to the experience bar...The only time I actually remember paying true attention to the XP bar was when I was charming bats or Xi Vius and coming back to the DSP zone to take out Goranga's...and I recall making 20% AA in an hour using that strategy.<br /><br />If I had to guess at what I'm making now, I would say it's no less than 1% every two kills depending on the mob...and seriously I'd place it at more like 3/4 of a percent per kill at 56...the "per hour" is probably even faster now that I had a revelation last night that I can take out anything undead in that zone and started working on the Vamps (and wow do they drop some nice items now and again...the best, of course, being no drop not useable by necro's *sigh*...got a couple of warriors who have started to worship me for those idol's they sometimes drop.<br /><br />Damage-wise, with the vamps I was pulling with snare, slowing, and occasionally trying to land a CoC but only half-heartedly since it never seems to stick...in reality, the pet was doing 90% of the damage.  Tonight, I think I'll replace Paralyzing Earth with Hungry Earth (D'oh!) and see how well that works (iirc, longer duration and does rather significant damage...).  I still like to CoC when I can for the STR debuff but really that and Bond of Death are the only things I'm casting...and while waiting for the vamps to repop I can pretty much chain pull bats, drudges, etc...<br /><br />I tried the Grey at 54 and didn't stay long...I got really ticked with all the adds I ended up getting (too many **** wanderers near the temple) but that's another really nice thing about Maiden's is that you are about as completely safe as you can get as long as you stay near the zone wall...I've been hunting at the first Coterie camp south of the DSP zone and the only time I get adds is if something that I don't see sees me pulling (the skeletons are a real pain for this since they are so small and the zone is so dark)...but they are rare at this camp so no biggie...and you're far enough from the DSP zone to have no real fear of trains...<br /><br />Root rotting = OMG SO BORING...I spent the better part of 55 at the howling stones zone in and I wanted to cry by the end of it...there's just no excitement in it...meanwhile, charming is rather exciting, decent exp, and fun, too!  At 54, you will get more resists than me and find charm breaking earlier but I can't really say whether it'll be enough to ruin the experience.  I am confident you would be able to handle a bat in ME at that level but you might want to stick to them until you get the hang of it.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
